5. Trailing commas: Although some parsers may accept it, a trailing comma after the last key-value pair in an object or the last element in an array is considered a syntax error in JSON.
6. Unescaped special characters: Special characters in strings need to be escaped with a backslash. Unescaped characters can cause parsing errors.

If the JSON file has any of these issues, it will be considered to have a structural error. If none of these issues are present, the JSON can be considered structurally sound.
